&lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;col-sm-12 col-md-12&quot;&gt;&lt;img id=&quot;bor&quot; src=&quot;data/uploads/innerbanner14.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;col-sm-12 col-md-12&quot;&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;1. Endoscopy is a procedure that lets your doctor look inside your body.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;2. It uses an instrument called an endoscope, or scope for short.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;3. Scopes have a tiny camera attached to a long, thin tube.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;4. The doctor moves it through a body passageway or opening to see inside an organ.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;5. Sometimes scopes are used for surgery, such as for removing polyps from the colon.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;h5&gt;Endoscopy Atlas&lt;/h5&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(% gallery name=Endoscopy-single %)(% gallery name=Endoscopy-double %)(% gallery name=Endoscopy-three %)&lt;/p&gt;
